when u start jquery u want to select ID or class in website u can write code like this

$(document).ready(function(){
    $("button").click(function(){
        $(".test").hide();
    });
});

in the first line

$(document).ready(function(){
    // method
});

to start the method u went to write in 

$(document).ready(function(){

    $("button").click(function(){
        $(".test").hide();
    });
    
});

after u write starter jquery , $("button") is selecter this mean all button and .click(funtion(){...}); is mean when u click this
it will do order in this funtion

selecter have 4 type
  1. $("button") = all button tag
  2. $(".button") = class button
  3. $("#button") = id button
  4. $(this) = Selects the current

tip
  1. $("*") = all element
  2. $("p.intro") = Selects all <p> elements with class="intro"
  3. $("ul li:first-child") = Selects the first <li> element of every <ul>
  4. $("tr:even") = Selects all even <tr> elements
  5. $("[href]") = Selects all elements with an href attribute
  6. $("a[target='_blank']") = Selects all <a> elements with a target attribute value equal to "_blank"
